{
  "texts": [
    "Integrating fairness and bias mitigation strategies from the outset of model development is crucial for building AI that aligns with ethical standards.",
    "The study advocates for a multidisciplinary approach to AI development, incorporating insights from ethics, social sciences, and diverse cultural perspectives to enrich the understanding and treatment of bias.",
    "Adopting transparent development processes, where models are auditable and their decisions explainable, can foster trust and accountability in AI technologies.",
    "Furthermore, the engagement of diverse user groups in testing and feedback cycles can unveil biases that may not be evident to developers, facilitating the creation of more inclusive AI.",
    "The establishment of ethical guidelines and best practices for AI development, informed by the latest research findings and societal expectations, can guide developers in navigating the ethical complexities of their work."
  ]
}